binding.p: BM in-house; brown leather binding, blind-tooled, with a pair toggles and loops fastening made from twisted leather. Spine: 'Baḥya ben Asher. Kad haḳ-ḳemaḥ Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 9932.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Gaster (b. 1856, d. 1939), scholar and rabbi: his manuscript, Cod. G. 88: inscribed with his name (folio 208v); purchased by the British Museum from him on 12 April, 1924: inscribed (back flyleaf [i]v).
